by British Alberta » Sat Feb 06, 2021 12:06 pm

Every division of the Peacekeeping Army shares a compositional pattern of a company of Babaylan. In Pre-European Filipino and Malaysian culture, the term Babaylan referred to Faith-Healers and Shamans who were specialists in the fields of culture, religion, medicine and all kinds of theoretical knowledge about the phenomenon of nature. Their function in the army is similar. The Babaylan are utilized as Field Medics, Technicians, Hackers, and Communications Experts. Their primary directive is to aid combatants on the field, and are not to be confused with Field Engineers, who are tasked with Repairs and Fortification. A Company is led by a Captain, or Kapitan; who reports directly to the Datu (Usually a Division/Regiment/Company Commander). Aside from their Field Duties, the Babaylan also function as the Tech Advisors to the Kapitan.

An interesting fact that i learned

In the Pan-Asiatic states, one of the prevailing "religious" theories is something called "god-building." The basic concept of god-building is the formalization of the process by which cults of personality or the like are formed; it's social engineering on the largest possible level. The processes by which religions are formed are on a meta-level identified and applied to the Pan-Asiatic States' Communist Party, and originated from Anatoly Lunacharsky's realization that given that if the aim of socialism is freedom then that freedom must include freedom to practice religion however one sees fit, but that nonetheless the religions of the old world have been corrupted by the old world order socialism seeks to overthrow, and that socialism's empirical approach to things should thusly be applied to religious practices in order to further the revolution- those faiths that survive, I assume, will be those that were not twisted to harm the proletariat, and thus deserve a place in the new socialist order.

Rather cool theory, all said. Internal self-consistence isn't something you see all too often in literary ideologies.
